3823. Reverse Letters Then Special Characters in a String
Solved
Easy
premium lock icon
Companies
Hint
You are given a string s consisting of lowercase English letters and special characters.

Your task is to perform these in order:

Reverse the lowercase letters and place them back into the positions originally occupied by letters.
Reverse the special characters and place them back into the positions originally occupied by special characters.
Return the resulting string after performing the reversals.

 Edge cases (already handled)

Only letters → reversing letters does nothing

Only special characters → whole string reversed

Single character → unchanged

Example 1:

Input: s = ")ebc#da@f("

Output: "(fad@cb#e)"

Explanation:

The letters in the string are ['e', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'a', 'f']:
Reversing them gives ['f', 'a', 'd', 'c', 'b', 'e']
s becomes ")fad#cb@e("
​​​​​​​The special characters in the string are [')', '#', '@', '(']:
Reversing them gives ['(', '@', '#', ')']
s becomes "(fad@cb#e)"
Example 2:

Input: s = "z"

Output: "z"

Explanation:

The string contains only one letter, and reversing it does not change the string. There are no special characters.

Example 3:

Input: s = "!@#$%^&*()"

Output: ")(*&^%$#@!"

Explanation:

The string contains no letters. The string contains all special characters, so reversing the special characters reverses the whole string.

 

Constraints:

1 <= s.length <= 100
s consists only of lowercase English letters and the special characters in "!@#$%^&*()".

Approach 1: 
Step 1: Fill stacks

Traverse the string once.

If character is a letter → push onto letterStack

Else → push onto specialStack

Step 2: Rebuild the string

Traverse the string again.

If original char was a letter → replace it with letterStack.top() and pop

Else → replace it with specialStack.top() and pop

class Solution {
public:
    string reverseByType(string s) {
        stack<char> letterSt, specialSt;

        for(char c : s){
            if(c>= 'a' && c<= 'z')
                letterSt.push(c);
            else
                specialSt.push(c);
        }

        for(char &c: s){
            if(c >= 'a' && c <= 'z'){
                c = letterSt.top();
                letterSt.pop();
            }else{
                c = specialSt.top();
                specialSt.pop();
            }
        }
        return s;
    }
};

Approach 2: 
Clean approach to solve it
High-level approach

Traverse the string

Collect all letters in one array

Collect all special characters in another array

Reverse both arrays

Traverse the string again

If original char was a letter, take next from reversed letters

Else take next from reversed specials

Build and return the result
Time: O(n)
Space: O(n)

class Solution {
public:
    string reverseLettersThenSpecial(string s) {
        string letters, specials;

        // Step 1: Separate characters
        for (char c : s) {
            if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z')
                letters.push_back(c);
            else
                specials.push_back(c);
        }

        // Step 2: Reverse both
        reverse(letters.begin(), letters.end());
        reverse(specials.begin(), specials.end());

        // Step 3: Rebuild string
        int l = 0, sp = 0;
        for (char &c : s) {
            if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z')
                c = letters[l++];
            else
                c = specials[sp++];
        }

        return s;
    }
};

Approach 3: 
class Solution {
public:
    string reverseLettersThenSpecial(string s) {
        int n = s.size();

        auto isLetter = [](char c) {
            return c >= 'a' && c <= 'z';
        };

        // Pass 1: reverse letters
        int i = 0, j = n - 1;
        while (i < j) {
            while (i < j && !isLetter(s[i])) i++;
            while (i < j && !isLetter(s[j])) j--;
            if (i < j) swap(s[i++], s[j--]);
        }

        // Pass 2: reverse special characters
        i = 0; j = n - 1;
        while (i < j) {
            while (i < j && isLetter(s[i])) i++;
            while (i < j && isLetter(s[j])) j--;
            if (i < j) swap(s[i++], s[j--]);
        }

        return s;
    }
};

